    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB DOOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601801" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB DOOR</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>When a door adjustment is required, you will need to know where the various adjustments are located
                and what effect each adjustment has on door fit. These adjustments apply whether door has been replaced
                or adjustment is simply being made to improve the door to frame fit or operation.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Door Hinge</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Forward and rearward door adjustments are made by shims (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601895">Item 1, Figure 95</hotlnk>) located between door half of hinge and door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601895" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601895" filename="../figg16/G1601895.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Forward/Rearward, Up/Down Door Adjustments</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ADJUSTING SHIMS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELONGATED HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HINGE BACK SIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE FRONT SIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DOOR HALF OF HINGE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Up and down door adjustment is made at elongated holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601895">Item 2, Figure 95</hotlnk>) in door half of hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601895">Item 5, Figure 95</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In and out door adjustment is made at enlarged holes and floating tapped plates (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601896">Item 3, Figure 96</hotlnk>) inside door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601896" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601896" filename="../figg16/G1601896.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="352px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. In/Out Door Adjustments</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HINGE MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB DOOR HINGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FLOATING TAPPED ADJUSTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR HINGE PILLAR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With 6 hinge mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601896">Item 1, Figure 96</hotlnk>) slightly loosened, adjust hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601896">Item 2, Figure 96</hotlnk>) to center door in opening with slight pressure
                    on weatherseal. Then tighten bolts to 180 in-lbs. (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
